  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca\u0db8\u0ddd\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0ddb\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The doctor died of pneumonia",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A doctor from the Sirimavo Bandaranaike Children's Hospital in Peradeniya died while receiving treatment at the Karapitiya Teaching Hospital, the health department said.",
        "The deceased was a 30-year-old doctor named Deepal Amarasuriya, a thinker of Thennakoon Mudiansela, a resident of Halyela.",
        "A post-mortem examination revealed that he had died of shock caused by a bacterial infection with pneumonia. The inquest into this death was conducted today (14) at the Galle Karapitiya Teaching Hospital by Additional Municipal Coroner Mr. Chandrasena Lokuge.",
        "The deceased doctor was a father of one. It was revealed during the autopsy that he had been treated for corona virus and had also contracted influenza a few weeks ago. Relatives have also said that the doctor, who has been waiting in petrol queues for several days, used a tube to take petrol from his car to the motorcycle.",
        "After that, he fell ill and developed pneumonia and was admitted to Peradeniya Hospital. He was later admitted to Kandy Hospital and Ekmo was transferred to Karapitiya Hospital on the 11th for treatment. He died this morning (14).",
        "The post-mortem examination of the dead doctor's body was conducted by expert forensic doctor Mrs. Janaki Warusahannadi."
      ],
